-- Sub-Saharan African Stocks Report: Housing Finance, Kenya Commercial Bank
-- Eric Ombok
-- 2010-06-15T16:01:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/sub-saharan-african-stocks-report-housing-finance-kenya-commercial-bank.html

          
          
             Kenya’s  All-Share Index  snapped four
days of gains, falling 0.1 percent to 73.91 at the close in
Nairobi.  
 Mauritius’s  SEMDEX Index  rose for the first day in seven,
advancing 0.5 percent to 1,623.04. The  Nigerian Stock Exchange
All-Share Index  rose for a third day, adding 0.3 percent to
25,526.19, while Namibia’s  FTSE/Namibia Overall Index  dropped
0.1 percent to 761.02 and the  Ghana Stock Exchange ’s All-Share
Index declined 0.7 percent to 6,467.29 at the close in Accra.  
 The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan Africa,
excluding South Africa. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  
 Housing Finance Ltd.  (HFCL KN), Kenya’s only publicly
traded mortgage company, gained 50 cents, or 4.8 percent, to
21.25 shillings. The company will increase lending to clients to
take advantage of incentives introduced in the East African
nation’s budget last week, Managing Director  Frank Ireri  said.  
 Kenya Commercial Bank Ltd.  (KNCB KN), the country’s biggest
lender by branches, rose as much as 2.4 percent to 21.25
shillings after saying existing shareholders can apply to
receive two shares for every five held at 17 shillings apiece in
a rights offer. The stock was unchanged at the close.  
